data.title: Good Eats!
data.text: Good down home cooking. An amazing breakfast menu and reasonably priced. Be sure to enjoy a milkshake in the afternoon....made the old fashioned way!

data.title: Great basic breakfast
data.text: It's been there for a LONG time and had great reviews so we had to give it a try when we were in town in May.  The food was good and you can't beat the price so we went again this visit in November and once again we weren't disappointed.  Nothing fancy but good food and service.

data.title: Great Food and Staff!
data.text: This cafe is my favorite place in Temecula Old Town to eat and relax.  Their food is fantastic and their staff is great!  Always welcomed and have never had anything but the best rafts!  I highly recommend walking around Old Town Temecula and grabbing a bite at the Swing Inn Great History here too!

data.title: Simple but good!!!
data.text: Temecula has a fun cafe.. Good food with great service.. More for breakfast for us.. Biscuits and gravy, excellent.. We love the old time feel.. Definitely an old establishment, but fun..

data.title: great breakfast
data.text: Been eating breakfast here for 20 years, the restaurant is one of the originals in town.  Eat breakfast here!

data.title: Great Breakfast!
data.text: It was a busy Labor Day weekend Saturday that we chose the Swing Inn Cafe based upon a suggestion from our hotel.  A party of 6, arriving around 9:30am, we only had to wait about 10 minutes for a table.  Classic breakfasts of eggs, bacon, sausage gravy and biscuits, pancakes, and huevos rancheros as a special, to name a few.  Everything was served quickly in a fast paced environment, with several servers taking care of our party of 6.  Coffees and waters were filled multiple times, without having to ask...and when a place is as busy as the Swing Inn was...that means a lot to me!  It was the perfect place for a Saturday gathering of a family group of 6.  Thanks Swing Inn! :)

data.title: This is the place to eat breakfast or go for the homemade pie
data.text: New to town we saw all the Harleys and knew it would be good, it was better than good!  As we walked in we saw fresh made pies and asked about banana whipped cream; we ended up with the biggest piece of banana chocolate peanut whipped cream pie you can imagine, lucky there was 2 of us to share.  We split a Spanish omelette which was big fluffy and perfectly done set with country potatoes done the way we like them, hot and fresh and sourdough toast. And the prices were way lower than other places!  Everything coming out looked awesome but the pie sold us!!

data.title: Step Back in time
data.text:
I was recommended the Swing Inn for breakfast and it didn't dissapoint. Food was good, service friendly and the milkshakes are delicious - if you try one, the chocolate is the best. 

Definitly worth a visit as it's in the heart of the old town which is like stepping back in time. It definitly sparks the imagination. Enjoy!

data.title: A Temecula classic who's time has come and gone.
data.text: The quality of the food is fair at best and the service isn't much better. As  far as atmosphere it is a quaint little diner and on the weekends a lot of old classic cars show up there.

data.title: Must visit for great food in Old Town Temecula
data.text:
We've eaten at the Swing Inn Café several times and love the food.  The environment is ... home town, rustic western café.   What I'd like to see is the political TV news channel changed to something less unwelcoming.  There's plenty on besides the news channel they have playing all day, or simply turn the TV off and allow patrons to enjoy their meals.

Some of the patrons can be low with their continued negative remarks about people, groups and politics in general, as though they continually spouting off about their own beliefs are going to change the minds of others around them.  It isn't and it can be annoying.

Besides that ... we like the place, enjoy eating meals there and return regardless but we know many, many people that have not returned because of what I typed above.

data.title: Great food, reasonable prices
data.text: Chose this place because they offered pastrami sandwiches, which I consider a delicacy.  We got a table immediately, though the place was almost full.  Service was quick and friendly, and my pastrami showed up in a short time along with a bowl of navy bean soup.  First the soup; remarkably good, laden with carrots and other veggies, very flavorful.  The pastrami; first rate, one of the best ever, served on excellent rye bread.  My travel partner had the steak sandwich, which also proved to be outstanding.  I had the lemonade to drink with my meal, a good choice.  This place seems to be a favorite with locals, and I can understand why.

data.title: Popular, clean, fast, tasty and friendly
data.text: We really enjoyed our breakfast in this little place in the main part of old temecula.   We got great service, very attentive considering how packed the place was.   Our food came out perfect and quick, my wife really like the breakfast burritto, I had standard eggs and sausage, great hash browns.   We will return next time in town, can't go wrong here for breakfast

data.title: Right in the middle of town.
data.text: Had a great meal at the Swing Inn Cafe.  It's a cute little diner right in the middle of Old Town Temecula.  They have consistently decent food.  The chef salad was pretty big and filled me up.  Service was great and the price was right.  I will definitely be back.

data.title: Awesome
data.text: This is an awesome place to hang out. The guys and gals are super friendly. They'll put a smile on your face. I love this cafe

data.title: Step back in time
data.text:
This place is open when other stores are not. the Swing Inn offered amazing breakfast
and we were so glad we chose to have a a bite to eat here before heading back to Las Vegas. The service was wonderful...so friendly .The food was great and their pies...yummy! Its simplistic and has a wonderful history. When you are there sip a cup of coffee and read all about their history which is creatively a part of their menu! Then walk outside and notice the pole wear cowboys tied up their horses. I enjoyed my step back in time and learning about Old Town Temecula and this quaint restaurant.

data.title: Great Eats!
data.text: Best omelettes, coffee and service in Old Town!  Optional bar, booth or outdoor eating, its all good.  Plenty of coffee, the guys and gals are all about the Service!

data.title: Our Go To Place when in Temecula
data.text: We always meet at Swing Inn Cafe when we come to town.  We have breakfast or lunch and then start our shopping, etc.  Before leaving, we always come back for another meal.  We love this cafe.  The people are so nice and the service is good.  Oh and the food is delicious too.

data.title: GREAT EATS -- ANY MEAL
data.text: Had breakfast, lunch and dinner and later night snacks at Swing Inn and found service, tasty food and pretty fair prices at all times. Easy parking and lots of seating -- gracious servers.

data.title: Great place
data.text: The Swing Inn has been a local meeting place for years located in Old Town Temecula. Visit the Farmers Market on Saturday mornings and the breakfast at the Swing Inn. Good company, great food, great service. Portions are large....order the kids meal it's big also.

data.title: BEST breakfast in town
data.text: We found this cool little place and loved it so much we came back for Sunday brunch several weeks in a row.
